@startuml
autonumber
actor "Prosumer" as P
box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box
box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "AssetLink MS" as ALMS
participant "Telemetry MS" as TMS
end box
box "Infrastructure Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS\n(AssetLink DB)" as ALDB
database "AWS RDS\n(Telemetry DB)" as TDB
queue "Kafka Cluster" as Kafka
end box

== Asset Link Provisioning / Decommissioning ==

note over P, Kafka: For Decommissioning, the same steps are executed in reverse order: Telemetry Consumer is deactivated \nfirst, then the Kafka Topic is deleted, and finally the AssetLink status is updated in RDS.

P -> Camunda: Trigger AssetLink\nManagement Process\n(Onboard/Offboard)
Camunda -> Kong: POST /assetlinks\n{prosumerId, assetId, utilityOperatorId, ZoneId}
Kong -> ALMS: Forward Request
ALMS -> ALDB: JDBC INSERT asset_link(id, prosumer_id, asset_id,\nutility_operator_id, ZoneId, status=ACTIVE)
note left: Decommissioning sets status=INACTIVE\nto prevent Zombie Assets.
ALDB --> ALMS: 200 OK
ALMS --> Kong: 200 OK 
Kong --> Camunda: 200 OK 

Camunda -> Kafka: Create Topic\n'{assetId}-{ZoneId}'
Kafka --> Camunda: Ack

Camunda -> Kong: POST /telemetry/consumers\n{topic: '{assetId}-{ZoneId}'}
Kong -> TMS: Forward Request
TMS -> Kafka: Subscribe to Topic\n'{assetId}-{ZoneId}'
note left: If Decommissioning, consumer is DEACTIVATED\ninstantly to prevent 'Zombie Assets' from\ndispatching phantom data.
Kafka --> TMS: Ack
TMS -> TDB: JDBC INSERT consumer\n(id, topic, status=ACTIVE)
TDB --> TMS: 200 OK
TMS --> Kong: 200 OK
Kong --> Camunda: Consumer State Updated
Camunda --> P: Asset Link\nProvisioned/Decommissioned
@enduml